hook.real_world_problem:
Zerodha trading API: POST /api/orders

```json
{
  "symbol": "RELIANCE",
  "quantity": 10,
  "orderType": "BUY",
  "accountBalance": 9999999.99  ← ATTACKER ADDED THIS!
}
```

Without validation: Spring maps ALL JSON fields to the Order entity.
Attacker can set their own `accountBalance` to 10 million rupees!

With `@JsonIgnoreProperties` + `@Valid` DTOs:
```java
@Data
public class OrderRequest {
    @NotBlank @Size(min=2, max=20) private String symbol;
    @Positive @Max(10000) private int quantity;
    @NotNull private OrderType orderType;
    // accountBalance field NOT HERE → ignored even if sent
}
// Attacker sends accountBalance: 9999999.99 → silently ignored!
```

concept_explanation.bean_validation:
**Bean Validation (@Valid):**

```java
public record PaymentRequest(
    @NotBlank(message='merchant_id is required')
    @Pattern(regexp='^MRC-[0-9]{3,}$', message='Invalid merchant ID format')
    String merchantId,

    @NotNull @Positive @DecimalMax('1000000.00')
    BigDecimal amount,

    @NotNull @Valid
    GatewayType gateway,

    @Size(max=500)
    @SafeHtml  // Hibernate Validator extension: strips XSS
    String description
) {}

@RestController
class PaymentController {
    @PostMapping('/api/payments')
    public Payment create(@RequestBody @Valid PaymentRequest req) {
        // @Valid: validates ALL constraints before method executes
        // Validation failure: throws MethodArgumentNotValidException → 400
    }
}

// Global exception handler:
@RestControllerAdvice
class ValidationExceptionHandler {
    @ExceptionHandler(MethodArgumentNotValidException.class)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST)
    public Map<String,String> handle(MethodArgumentNotValidException ex) {
        return ex.getBindingResult().getFieldErrors().stream()
            .collect(Collectors.toMap(
                FieldError::getField,
                fe -> fe.getDefaultMessage()));
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.sql_injection:
**SQL injection prevention:**

```java
// VULNERABLE (never do this):
String query = 'SELECT * FROM payments WHERE merchant = '' + merchantId + ''';
// Attack: merchantId = '' OR '1'='1 → returns ALL payments!

// SAFE with JPA (parameterized queries):
@Query('SELECT p FROM Payment p WHERE p.merchantId = :merchantId')
List<Payment> findByMerchant(@Param('merchantId') String merchantId);
// JPA/Hibernate: always uses PreparedStatement with ? parameters
// SQL injection: impossible with parameterized queries

// If you MUST use native SQL:
@Query(value='SELECT * FROM payments WHERE merchant_id = :id', nativeQuery=true)
List<Payment> findNative(@Param('id') String id);
// Still safe: Spring Data uses PreparedStatement binding
```

